romainfrancois commented on issue #4492: ARROW-5509: [R] Add basic write_parquet
URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/4492#issuecomment-501246293


   Maybe it would be worth dealing with the `ARROW_R_WITH_PARQUET` similarly to what we now do with `ARROW_R_WITH_ARROW`, i.e. instead of having: 
   
   ```cpp
   // [[arrow::export]]
   void write_parquet_file(const std::shared_ptr<arrow::Table>& table,
                           std::string filename) {
   #ifdef ARROW_R_WITH_PARQUET
      // ... real code using parquet
   #else
     // ... error 
   #endif
   }
   ```
   
   we could have e.g. 
   
   
   ```cpp
   // [[parquet::export]]
   void write_parquet_file(const std::shared_ptr<arrow::Table>& table,
                           std::string filename) {
       // ... real code using parquet
   }
   ```
   
   or maybe give an argument to `arrow::export` e.g. 
   
   ```cpp
   // [[arrow::export(PARQUET)]]
   void write_parquet_file(const std::shared_ptr<arrow::Table>& table,
                           std::string filename) {
       // ... real code using parquet
   }
   ```

